.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS build
.PP
.I Compose a Unified Kernel Image from a kernel + initrd + cmdline
.PP
.B Category:
UKI
.br
.B Maturity:
beta
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-uki\-build build OUTPUT.efi \-\-kernel PATH [\-\-initrd PATH]... [\-\-cmdline STR] [\-\-osrel PATH] [\-\-splash PATH] [\-\-backend ukify|objcopy]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B OUTPUT.efi
Output UKI path
.TP
.B \-\-kernel PATH
Source kernel vmlinuz (required)
.TP
.B \-\-initrd PATH
Source initrd (repeatable for multi\-initrd concat)
.TP
.B \-\-cmdline STR
Kernel cmdline to embed (default: empty)
.TP
.B \-\-osrel PATH
os\-release file (default: /etc/os\-release)
.TP
.B \-\-uname STR
Kernel version for .uname
.TP
.B \-\-splash PATH
BMP splash image (optional)
.TP
.B \-\-dtb PATH
Device tree blob (optional)
.TP
.B \-\-stub PATH
EFI stub binary (default: auto\-detect systemd\-stub)
.TP
.B \-\-backend ukify
\-\-backend ukify
.TP
.B objcopy
Build backend (default: auto — ukify if available)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-uki\-build build /boot/efi/EFI/Linux/custom.efi \-\-kernel /boot/vmlinuz\-6.12 \-\-initrd /boot/initramfs\-6.12.img \-\-cmdline \'root=UUID=abc ro quiet\'
lamboot\-uki\-build build /tmp/test.efi \-\-kernel /boot/vmlinuz\-$(uname \-r) \-\-initrd /boot/initrd.img\-$(uname \-r)
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Wraps ukify (preferred) or objcopy (fallback). Produces UKIs per UAPI.5 spec that work with any UKI\-aware bootloader.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Runs unprivileged
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
inspect, sign, verify, lamboot\-signing\-keys
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/uki-build/build
.UE
